sect2.para:
In the core Java library is an interface called CharSequence. Here is a shortened version
of that interface:

  java.lang.CharSequence (abbreviated)

    interface CharSequence {
      char charAt(int index);
      int length();
    }


Now suppose someone put forward the question, What is a CharSequence? Notice the potential
here for equivocation. Well it's an interface! might be an appropriate response. A follow-up
question might be Is String a CharSequence? Of course, the answer is
yes, so String is a CharSequence and
CharSequence is an interface, therefore, String is an interface.
I hope you see the problem here.
